  "notes": "Yazdi Persian (Yazdī). Yazd — central Iranian plateau. Zoroastrian heartland; some archaic features in Zoroastrian community speech ('Dari' of Zoroastrians — not Afghan Dari). /æ/ → [a] (conservative, like Shirazi/Kermani). /q/ somewhat preserved in older/conservative speech.",
